-- Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Credicorp, Relapasa, Southern Copper
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-01-06T19:05:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-06/peru-stocks-atacocha-credicorp-relapasa-southern-copper.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:42 p.m.  Lima  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.1 percent to 19,914.66. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  dropped 0.9 percent to 2,554.66.  Banks, miners and industrial shares declined on investor
concern the European debt crisis may worsen, said Arlen Lahura,
a trader at Lima-based brokerage Coril SAB.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, fell 3.1 percent to $105.40.  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (CMA\B) 
(ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc mining company, dropped 2.5
percent to 77 centimos.  Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), the
country’s biggest producer of the metal, slid 1.7 percent to
$30.81.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1)  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA, fell 1.1 percent to 90 centimos after crude declined in
 New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
